 cool (approx. 30 minutes). Place into refrigerator until ready to use.","Remove cheesecake from freezer 15-30 minutes before serving to soften. Drizzle coulis over cheesecake and decorate with remaining 50 g blueberries just before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Frozen yoghurt","content":["40 g white sugar","250 g cream cheese","200 g Greek yoghurt","250 g double cream","1 pinch coarse salt","1 tsp natural vanilla extract"]},{"title":"Biscuit base","content":["85 g unsalted butter, softened, plus extra for greasing","150 g gingernut biscuits","200 g frozen blueberries"]},{"title":"Blueberry coulis","content":["20 g lemon juice","2 tsp icing sugar","350 g frozen blueberries"]}],"id":"r106761","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-U99PYkFRyqc\/XZWcr5TIvMI\/AAAAAAAAedU\/KML-5rRMHNAuu8Nll_mYY1knKTqXZISegCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_4EtM1xiEfDnDp0r3.png","title":"Blueberry frozen yoghurt cheesecake","publishedAt":"2016-11-20T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8.87 g","fat":"41.28 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"28.2 g","calories":"2164 kJ \/ 515 kcal"},"usefulItems":"shallow freezable containers (e.g. plastic, silicone), plastic wrap, springform cake tin (20 cm), baking paper, bowl, jug, fine mesh sieve, freezer, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Replace gingernut biscuits with gluten free biscuits to make this a gluten free dessert."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","14h 55m","8 slices"]}